  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Localised preparedness and response to primary and secondary impacts of COVID-19 - CLHEI</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Christian Aid and its partners will deliver a 5-month Health, WASH and Social Protection programme to mitigate COVID-19 impact with IDPs and vulnerable hard-to- reach communities in 12 LGAs within Benue, Kaduna and Maiduguri States. Using integrated, adaptive rapidly scalable approaches leveraging on national and community partner networks, faith/ traditional leaders, youth (prioritizing women and girls), displaced, socially excluded, elderly, people with disabilities and underlying health conditions. Intervention approach fully in line with Grand Bargain commitment of more support and funding tools to local and national responders.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. Enhanced COVID 19 risk communication and community engagement, and accountability measures for vulnerable population
2. Improved capacity of community and local health systems to effectively identify and refer COVID 19 related cases in line with government protocols and sustain access to essential health services to vulnerable groups

3. Vulnerable households are enabled to access basic needs and safeguarded from the impact of lockdowns and strict containment measures.</narrative>
  </description>
